# Comprehensive Data Element Catalog

- The canonical catalog is `config/comprehensive_data_element_list.json`.
- Treat it as exhaustive across all source payloads Cortex can read, including nested objects/arrays and Salesforce comprehensive category fields.
- When adding/changing payload structures (Pendo, Jira, CSR, LeanDNA, Salesforce, portfolio), update the catalog in the same change.
- Do not collapse a source to top-level blobs when field-level paths exist and are used by hydrate/mapping.
- If a generated or derived dictionary/doc is incomplete, fix the catalog first, then regenerate/update docs.
